Mix crumbs and butter; press firmly onto bottom and halfway up side of lightly greased 9-inch springform pan. Refrigerate. Reserve 6 strawberries for garnish; mash remaining strawberries. Stir boiling water into dry gelatin in large bowl at least 2 min. until completely dissolved. Add ice cubes; stir until melted. Add whipped topping and mashed strawberries; stir gently with wire whisk until well blended. Refrigerate 10 min. or until mixture is very thick and will mound. Spoon into prepared crust. Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm. Remove side of pan. Slice each of the reserved strawberries in half. Arrange strawberries, cut side down, around top of cake. Drizzle strawberries with melted chocolate.